        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: resize cost history menu card to the hovered day's content",
        "body": "  ## Summary\r\n\r\n  Resize the cost history menu card to the hovered day's actual content instead\r\n  of reserving a fixed worst-case height, so the menu row grows and shrinks with\r\n  the selected day's model breakdown.\r\n\r\n  ## Implementation\r\n\r\n   - Updated `Sources/CodexBar/CostHistoryChartMenuView.swift`\r\n   - Computed total card height deterministically from fixed component heights\r\n    (`totalCardHeight`) rather than padding every day to the tallest breakdown\r\n   - Dropped the filler-row / `maxRenderedBreakdownRows` machinery and derived\r\n    detail height from the selected day's visible rows, capped at the viewport\r\n    limit\r\n   - Defaulted the selection to the latest day and reported height changes from\r\n    the hover handler via a new `onHeightChange` callback\r\n   - Updated `Sources/CodexBar/StatusItemController+MenuPresentation.swift`\r\n   - Routed the measured height through `MenuHostingView.intrinsicContentSize`,\r\n    which is the size NSMenu actually honors for custom-view rows\r\n   - Added `applyMeasuredHeight` to update the frame and invalidate the\r\n  intrinsic\r\n    size together\r\n   - Updated `Sources/CodexBar/StatusItemController+HostedSubmenus.swift`\r\n   - Wired the chart's `onHeightChange` to the hosting view through a weak\r\n  relay,\r\n    breaking the init-time cycle between the SwiftUI view and its host\r\n\r\n  ## Why\r\n\r\n  NSMenu's modal tracking run loop never delivers SwiftUI `onPreferenceChange`,\r\n  so the card couldn't measure itself live while open and instead reserved the\r\n  tallest possible height for every day — leaving short days padded with blank\r\n  space. Because every component height is fixed, computing the total directly\r\n  and resizing from the hover handler lets the row match the day under the\r\n  cursor.\r\n\r\n  ## Testing\r\n\r\n  - Ran `swift test --filter CostHistoryChartMenuViewTests`\r\n  - Swift Testing reported 3 tests in 1 suite passed\r\n  - Ran `make check`\r\n\r\n  ## Screenshots\r\nNow:\r\n<img width=\"311\" height=\"265\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-17 at 1 29 10 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6db5826d-dd88-4828-a779-9971636f5cfb\" />\r\n<img width=\"312\" height=\"350\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-17 at 1 29 01 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c9db6064-2e1b-42eb-b9b7-d02edb0d0745\" />\r\n<img width=\"312\" height=\"295\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-17 at 1 28 52 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2bf0dd07-f40c-42b8-90cf-6e054f4d7885\" />",
